<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="532" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,151,285]" pageId="11" pageNumber="532">
COMMENTS: The TL was correctly restricted to Umlalazi (uMlalazi) River by 
<bibRefCitation author="Gyldenstolpe, N." box="[1095,1331,151,177]" pageId="11" pageNumber="532" pagination="264 - 292" refId="ref28785" refString="Gyldenstolpe, N. (1934) The travels and collections of Johan August Wahlberg, 1810 - 1856: a pioneer naturalist in South Africa. Ibis, 76, 264 - 292. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1474 - 919 X. 1934. tb 01567. x" type="journal article" year="1934">Gyldenstolpe (1934)</bibRefCitation>
, but was incorrectly dated. Sundevall generally meticulously copied Wahlberg’s data, but he misread the date and locality on the specimen label, recording the date as 
<date box="[657,804,222,249]" pageId="11" pageNumber="532" value="1842-04-05">5 April 1842</date>
, although it is clearly 
<date box="[1058,1262,222,249]" pageId="11" pageNumber="532" value="1842-11-05">
5 November 
<quantity box="[1206,1262,223,249]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.67868" pageId="11" pageNumber="532" unit="in" value="1842.0">1842</quantity>
</date>
in his personal accessions register (
<figureCitation box="[375,474,259,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="11.[151,250,514,538]" captionTargetBox="[151,1425,306,487]" captionTargetId="figure-76@11.[151,1436,306,487]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 2. Sundevall’s personal acquisition catalogue, in which he recorded the date of the lectotype of Megalaema bilineata Sundevall as 4 November 1842." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6541741" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6541741/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="532">Figure 2</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6541741" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6541741" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6541741/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="532" startId="11.[151,250,514,538]" targetBox="[151,1425,306,487]" targetPageId="11">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,514,574]" pageId="11" pageNumber="532">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,275,514,538]" pageId="11" pageNumber="532">FIGURE 2.</emphasis>
Sundevall’s personal acquisition catalogue, in which he recorded the date of the lectotype of 
<taxonomicName authority="Sundevall" authorityName="Sundevall" authorityYear="1850" class="Aves" family="Megalaimidae" genus="Megalaema" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Piciformes" pageId="11" pageNumber="532" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bilineata">
<emphasis box="[1220,1436,514,538]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="532">Megalaema bilineata</emphasis>
Sundevall
</taxonomicName>
as 4 November 1842.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,620,754]" pageId="11" pageNumber="532">
<bibRefCitation author="Gyldenstolpe, N." box="[199,432,620,647]" pageId="11" pageNumber="532" pagination="1 - 116" refId="ref28755" refString="Gyldenstolpe, N. (1926) Types of birds in the Royal Natural History Museum in Stockholm. Arkiv f or Zoologi, 19, 1 - 116." type="journal article" year="1926">Gyldenstolpe (1926)</bibRefCitation>
repeated the date error in his catalogue of the 
<typeStatus box="[973,1021,621,647]" pageId="11" pageNumber="532">type</typeStatus>
specimens in the NRM. Wahlberg’s original labels are missing, but a rewritten label is correct regarding date and place. Wahlberg was at Tswaing, in 
<collectingRegion box="[151,357,692,718]" country="South Africa" name="Gauteng" pageId="11" pageNumber="532">Gauteng Province</collectingRegion>
, on 
<date box="[407,555,692,719]" pageId="11" pageNumber="532" value="1842-04-05">5 April 1842</date>
, and had been there since early 
<date box="[924,1065,692,718]" pageId="11" pageNumber="532" value="1842-03">March 1842</date>
, leaving for the Magaliesberg in early April.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
